If you use `getMany` on the query builder you will get an empty array if there are no results. For example:

``` ts
public async checkAtLeastOne(value: string): Promise<boolean> {
    const result = await getConnection()
        .getRepository(Entity)
        .createQueryBuilder('entity')
        .where('entity.value= :value', { value: value})
        .getMany();
    return result.length >= 1;
}
```
If you want one result and use `getOne` on the query builder then you can check if it is undefined. For example: 

``` ts
public async checkIfExists(value: string): Promise<boolean> {
    const result = await getConnection()
        .getRepository(Entity)
        .createQueryBuilder('entity')
        .where('entity.value= :value', { value: value})
        .getOne();
    return result !== undefined;
}
```

```I would like to know if there is any way to know if my query return a result or not```

You could use a count query to check how many rows you would fetch. This is the fastest option out of all the API calls.

```
public async checkIfExists(value: string): Promise<boolean> {
    return await getConnection()
        .getRepository(Entity)
        .createQueryBuilder('entity')
        .where('entity.value= :value', { value: value})
        .getCount() > 0;
}
```

