Parameters must be unique. The way you can change your code:

```ts
s.split(' ').forEach((token, index) => {
      const parameterName = "token" + index;
      queryBuilder.andWhere(new Brackets(tokenQb => {
        tokenQb.where('person.name ILIKE :' + parameterName);
        tokenQb.orWhere('person.lastName ILIKE :' + parameterName);
      })).setParameter(parameterName, token);
    });
```

> Parameters must be unique. The way you can change your code:
> 
> ```ts
> s.split(' ').forEach((token, index) => {
>       const parameterName = "token" + index;
>       queryBuilder.andWhere(new Brackets(tokenQb => {
>         tokenQb.where('person.name ILIKE :' + parameterName);
>         tokenQb.orWhere('person.lastName ILIKE :' + parameterName);
>       })).setParameter(parameterName, token);
>     });
> ```

@pleerock why should be the parameters unique? Programatically the parameter naming belongs to the it own 'where' function scope. If you would like to use a huge parameter bag you have to use query level naming despite of function scope level.

