You have a wrong entity. First, you forgot to use `@JoinColumn` - its required for use on one side of one-to-one relation. Second, you don't need a `@Column` decorator on a relation. Third, relations are OBJECTS, not "email".

```ts
@Entity()
export class Token {
    @PrimaryGeneratedColumn()
    public id: number;
    @OneToOne(type => User, user => user.token)
    @JoinColumn()
    public user: User;
    @Column()
    public token: string;
}

@Entity()
export class User {
    @PrimaryGeneratedColumn()
    public id: number;
    @Column({ unique: true })
    public email: string;
    @OneToOne(type => Token, token => token.user)
    public token: Token;
}
```

If you want to bind them via `email` instead of `id` use following code:


```ts
    @OneToOne(type => User, user => user.token)
    @JoinColumn({ referencedColumnName: "email" })
    public user: User;
}
