How do you do it in your database using sql? I guess its something like:

```ts
@Column({ type: "timestamp", default: () => "CURRENT_TIMESTAMP"))
time: string;
```

`() => ` syntax for `default` allows to use SQL expressions.

FYI, for those looking as of Tuesday, February 2, 2021, for some reason TypeORM converts `default: () => "CURRENT_TIMESTAMP"` to `now()` when using postgres 9.6. This meant that TypeORM generates new migrations changing their default type from `now()` to `CURRENT_TIMESTAMP` every time you try to generate new migrations.

The fix for us was to use this instead:

```ts
@Column({ type: "timestamp", default: () => "now()"))
time: string;
```

In MySQL 8:
```
@Column('date', { default: () => '(CURRENT_DATE)' })
last_date: Date;
```

For postgres I first created a migration with
```
@Column('date', { default: () => 'CURRENT_DATE::text::date' })
last_date: Date;
```
This created the column in postgres as `default ((CURRENT_DATE))`, then I changed the code to
```
@Column('date', { default: () => '((CURRENT_DATE))' })
last_date: Date;
```
With this change, the TypeORM generated default and the default on postgres are both `((CURRENT_DATE))`, so no migrations are created afterward.

When creating a table using `queryRunner` on Postgres, I didn't need to use `() => ` to get an expression default:

```TypeScript
await queryRunner.createTable(
  new Table({
  name: 'my-table',
  columns: [
    {
      name: "status",
      default: "'created'", // constant default
      type: "text"
    },
    {
      name: "created_at",
      type: "timestamp(0) without time zone",
      default: 'now()' // expression default
    }
  ]
  }),
  true, true, true
)
```

You can do 
```
@Column({ type: "timestamp", default: () => "now()" })
time: Date;
```

Have in mind this is not the same as doing:
```
@Column({ type: "timestamp", default: "now()" })
time: Date;
```

This last option in my case at least throw error in CI because it wasn't doing what it looks, so try going with the first alternative I mentioned.

